Eyewitnesses say it appeared the deceased swallowed drugs that police were trying to confiscate as he was being arrested. CAPE TOWN Cape Town police have opened an inquest into the death of a 33-year-old man on the Grand Parade in the Cape Town city centre on Thursday morning.They say it s suspected he died from a drug overdose. Eyewitnesses say it appeared the man swallowed drugs that police were trying to confiscate as he was being arrested. Police say a post-mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death. Another man was arrested at the scene on charges of malicious damage to property for allegedly damaging a marked metro police vehicle. Police fired rubber bullets to disperse an angry crowd that gathered.